<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Inline-block replaced elements with auto height and width</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#inline-replaced-height" />
        <meta name="flags" content="image" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify height is the intrinsic height when an inline-block replaced element with and intrinsic height and has a height and width computed as auto." />
        <style type="text/css">
            div
            {
                border: 3px solid green;
            }
            img
            {
                display: inline-block;
                height: auto;
                width: auto;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the top and bottom edges of the blue box touch the inner edges of the green border.</p>
        <div>
            <img alt="Test Image" src="../../../Support/blue100x33.png" />
        </div>
    </body>
</html>